Browserify support source map, but still I feel that this is drawback with browserify.
Is it possible to multiple files instead of single bundled file?
Currently it is not possible.
So, We can follow an alternate syntax by which will can generate multiple files.
Here is my proposal,

Let suppose we have `square.js`

``` js
var multiply = require('./multiply');
module.exports = function (n) {
  return multiply(n, n);
};
```

We can transform this module into browser module by following steps.
- Step 1 - copy whole file into an anonymous function like this,

``` js
define("square", function(){  //Extra line 1
   var multiply = require('./multiply');
   module.exports = function (n) {
     return multiply(n, n);
   };
}); //Extra line 2
```
- Step 2 - Replace "module.exports =" by "return"

``` js
define("square", function(){
   var multiply = require('./multiply');
   return function (n) {
     return multiply(n, n);
   };
})
```

So this is my initial thought process on source transformation, 

Alternately, we can do like this, using dependency injection,

``` js
define("square", function(multiply){
   return function (n) {
     return multiply(n, n);
   };
})
```
